Reasoning: 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is the most likely category as the paper deals with algorithms for solving parity games and analyses the data structures used in these algorithms. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is also likely as parity games are a well-studied topic in logic and the paper deals with the complexity of solving them. 
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is another possible category as parity games are a type of game and the paper deals with algorithms for solving them. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as solving parity games is a problem that arises in AI applications such as model checking and synthesis. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is also a possible category as the paper deals with the complexity of solving parity games and the size of the data structures used in the algorithms.
